title: Dimmu Borgir - Council Of Wolves And Snakes (EP)2018
description:
Dimmu Borgir - Council Of Wolves And Snakes (EP)2018

Dimmu Borgir Norwegian: is a Norwegian symphonic black metal band from Oslo, Norway, formed in 1993. The name is derived from Dimmuborgir, a volcanic formation in Iceland, the name of which means "dark cities In Old Norse. The band has been through numerous lineup changes over the years; guitarist Silenoz and vocalist Shagrath are the only original members who still remain with guitarist Galder being a longstanding member.

On 18 December 2017 it was announced that the first single from the new album will be initially released on a 7-inch vinyl E.P, and will be titled ‘Interdimensional Summit’, and it will be released on February 23, 2018.
Also Analogkid will create and release a Compilation to mark the event. The new album will be titled Eonian and will be released on 4 May through Nuclear Blast, which will mark the band’s first new release of original material in almost 8 years.On March 31 analogkid will release the concluson of The Interdimentional Cover up EP...

Council Of Wolves And Snakes

Current members

Official members

Shagrath – drums (1993–1995), lead vocals (1995–present), lead guitar (1995–1996)
Silenoz – rhythm guitar (1993–present), lead vocals (1993–1995)
Galder – lead guitar (2000–present)
Daray – drums (2008–present)
Gerlioz – keyboards, synthesizer (2010–present)

Session members
Cyrus – bass, backing vocals (2010–present)
